<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1323,1440,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42">
Newly recorded in Nova 
<collectingCountry box="[650,723,1601,1627]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="11" pageNumber="42">Scotia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[748,861,1601,1627]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[264,367,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[445,1140,1040,1608]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[440,1147,1035,1608]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution of Necrobia violacea and N. rufipes in the Maritime Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175106/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="42">
Figure 
<number box="[845,861,1601,1627]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Associated with carrion, they are saprophagous and predaceous (
<bibRefCitation author="Opitz" box="[652,799,1641,1667]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" refString="Opitz, W. (2002) Cleridae Latreille 1804. In: Arnett, R. H., Jr., Thomas, M. C., Skelley, P. E. &amp; Frank, J. H. (E ds.). American Beetles, Volume 2: Polyphaga: Scarabaeoidea through Curculionoidea. CRC Press, Boca Raton, USA. pp. 267 - 280." type="journal article" year="2002">
Opitz 
<number box="[735,799,1641,1667]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Found on the skins and bones of dead animals, a predator of dermestid larvae; a pest on grain, silk, and food (
<bibRefCitation author="Knull" box="[1109,1249,1681,1707]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" refString="Knull, J. N. (1951) The checkered beetles of Ohio (Coleoptera: Cleridae). Ohio Biological Survey Bulletin, 8 (42), 268 - 350." type="journal article" year="1951">
Knull 
<number box="[1186,1249,1681,1707]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42" value="1951.0">1951</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This originally Palearctic species is now cosmopolitan. Known in 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1147,1721,1747]" name="Canada" pageId="11" pageNumber="42">Canada</collectingCountry>
(Ontario and Qu√©bec) since at least 
<number box="[527,586,1761,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42" value="1895.0">1895</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wickham" box="[601,786,1761,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" refString="Wickham, H. F. (1895) The Coleoptera of Canada: XIII. The Cleridae of Ontario and Quebec. The Canadian E ntomologist, 27, 247 - 253." type="journal article" year="1895">
Wickham 
<number box="[723,786,1761,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="42" value="1895.0">1895</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
